HEADWORD: Tramroad
<hw>Tram"road`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Tram</ets> a
coal wagon + <ets>road</ets>.]</ety> <def>A road prepared for easy
transit of trams or wagons, by forming the wheel tracks of smooth beams
of wood, blocks of stone, or plates of iron.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tramway</ent>⟦br⟧
